[SIZE=5][B]ItemMagnet[/B] — Tiered Item Magnets, Redstone Fuel & Claim Protection[/SIZE]

[CENTER][I]v1.2.1 · Paper 1.21.1+ · Java 21+[/I][/CENTER]

[HR]

[SIZE=4][B]What is ItemMagnet?[/B][/SIZE]

ItemMagnet adds [B]craftable tiered magnet tools[/B] that pull nearby dropped items toward the player with [B]visible, line-of-sight physics[/B] — items slide around corners and stop at walls instead of teleporting through blocks.

Charge your resonator with [B]redstone dust[/B] (sneak + right-click, either hand) or let it [B]auto-absorb[/B] redstone from the ground. [B]Redstone blocks[/B] trigger a [B]power surge[/B]: extra charge plus a temporary radius boost shown on the item lore.

Built for survival SMPs that need [B]Lands[/B], [B]WorldGuard[/B], [B]Towny[/B], and [B]GriefPrevention[/B] respect out of the box — with an [B]in-game config GUI[/B], presets, unlock gates, and a developer API.

[HR]

[SIZE=4][B]Highlights[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]Three tiers[/B] — Fragment, Survey, Anchor (fully configurable materials, names, radius, drain)
[*][B]Live item lore[/B] — charge, boost timer, and current pull radius update in real time
[*][B]Hold modes[/B] — main hand, any hotbar slot, or anywhere in inventory (passive magnet)
[*][B]XP orb pulling[/B] — optional experience orb collection at the same radius
[*][B]Redstone fuel loop[/B] — dust recharge, block power surge, per-fuel sounds
[*][B]Claim-aware[/B] — Lands, WorldGuard, Towny, and GriefPrevention hooks
[*][B]In-game config GUI[/B] — [CODE]/itemmagnet config[/CODE] for settings, tiers, fuel, integrations
[*][B]Rename items[/B] — change tier display names from the GUI (chat input, color codes)
[*][B]Unlock gates[/B] — permission, advancement, CMI stat/rank, or admin command (persisted)
[*][B]Anti-AFK[/B] — optional movement check with one-time notify (no spam)
[*][B]PlaceholderAPI[/B] — charge, radius, tier, boost placeholders
[*][B]Developer API[/B] — cancellable pull, fuel absorb, deplete, and XP pull events
[/LIST]

[HR]

[SIZE=4][B]How it plays[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST=1]
[*]Unlock or craft a tier resonator (Fragment → Survey → Anchor)
[*]Hold the magnet (main hand, hotbar, or inventory — your choice)
[*]Fuel with redstone dust (sneak + right-click) or pick up redstone drops
[*]Drop items nearby — they [B]slide[/B] toward you with particles and optional arm swing
[*]Use a redstone block for a [B]power surge[/B] — bigger radius for a limited time
[*]Magnets respect claim borders — pull stops at Lands/WG/Towny/GP boundaries
[/LIST]

[I]Tip: Run [CODE]/itemmagnet debug[/CODE] to see your active magnet's tier, charge, radius, and protection state.[/I]

[HR]

[B]Requirements[/B]
[LIST]
[*][B]Paper 1.21.1+[/B] (not Spigot/CraftBukkit)
[*][B]Java 21+[/B]
[*]Tested on Paper 1.21.1, 1.21.4, and 26.1
[/LIST]

